                            <comment id="13841814" author="mate" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 22:36:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A test case to demonstrate the issue is now available here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mjiderhamn/classloader-leak-prevention/blob/master/src/test/java/se/jiderhamn/classloader/leak/prevention/CXFAuthenticatorTest.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mjiderhamn/classloader-leak-prevention/blob/master/src/test/java/se/jiderhamn/classloader/leak/prevention/CXFAuthenticatorTest.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13842119" author="mate" created="Sat, 7 Dec 2013 07:25:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Version 1.9.0 of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mjiderhamn/classloader-leak-prevention&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mjiderhamn/classloader-leak-prevention&lt;/a&gt; should now provide a workaround for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13875300" author="dkulp" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2014 21:57:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Little more reflection magic and I think this is now resolved.  Confirmation would be great.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13875993" author="mate" created="Sun, 19 Jan 2014 19:48:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Running my leak detecting test case against the 2.6.x SVN sources, it seems that setting loader.acc to null does the trick.&lt;br/&gt;
I have yet to test this in a deployed environment (possibly AccessController.doPrivileged() also makes a difference then) but likely the problem has been fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
